    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWe have upstreamed nearly every functionality from https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/playground, except for the query editor. Adding a (minimal) version allows archiving this project.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWe need a function, e.g., `:EditQuery` that\r\n\r\n* opens a `nofile` buffer with `ft=query` and the query linter attached;\r\n* runs the contents as a treesitter query (e.g., on `InsertLeave`) on the \"base buffer\" from which it is opened;\r\n* highlights any matches in the base buffer for the capture under the cursor in the editor buffer;\r\n* (optional) can be opened from `:InspectTree` via, e.g., `o`.\r\n\r\nIn contrast to `nvim-treesitter/playground`, I don't think we should make these queries persistent (i.e., allow saving them to the user's config directory).",
    "closed_at": null,
